description.value: East Greek terracotta figure vase (plastic vase). Complete small vase (apart from rim) in the form of head and shoulders of gorgoneion. She wears a headband in front of crudely depicted snakes, two of which rise to her chin. Her mouth is open with tongue thrust out between two long teeth sticking up from her mandible. She has almond shaped eyes. Mould-made and hollow. Traces of red paint on her 'hair'. White residue on her chin probably post depositional. Pale orange clay fabric with abundant silver mica, black and coarse white inclusions.
